ons of Val Doonican]]: ''Jump Ararnd'' (2013)\n* [[The Rails]]: ''Fair Warning'' (2014)\n* [[The Bar-Steward Sons of Val Doonican]]: ''The Devil Went Darn To Barnsley'' (2015)\n\n; DVDs\n* ''In Search of English Folk Song'' (1997 BBC film directed by [[Ken Russell]])\n: Fairport Convention, Donovan, Osibisa, Eliza Carthy, The Albion Band, Waterson\u2013Carthy, Edward II.\n: Reissued on DVD in 2008, but for Region 1 only\n\n;Topic Records 70 year anniversary boxed set ''[[Three Score and Ten]]'' issued in 2009\nCarthy appears a number of times\n*''Anglicana'' is one of the albums.<ref name = \"Three Score and Ten Accompanying Book\">{{cite web|url=http://www.topicrecords.co.uk/category/three-score-ten|title=Topic Records \u00bb THREE SCORE & TEN|website=Topicrecords.co.uk|accessdate=7 June 2018}}</ref>{{rp|90}} \n*\"Worcester City\" from ''Anglicana'' is track eleven on the seventh CD.\nwith Ben Ivitsky\n*\"Two Tears\" from ''Dreams of Breathing Underwater'' is track six on the sixth CD.\nAs Part of Waterson\u2013Carthy\n*Waterson:Carthy is one of the albums.\n*\"We Poor Labouring Men\" from ''Broken Ground'' is track twenty one on the sixth CD.\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.eliza-carthy.com|Eliza Carthy}} \u2013 official site\n*{{Official website|http://www.watersoncarthy.com|Waterson\u2013Carthy}} \u2013 official site\n*{{Discogs artist}}\n*[http://www.itvlocal.com/wales/newsextra/?player=WAL_NewsExtra_15&void=236768 Eliza Carthy] interview about her latest work, September 2008\n*[https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/release/wvmq ''Dreams Of Breathing Underwater''], BBC online review\n*[https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-eliza-carthy-dreams-of-breathing-underwater-topic-851873.html ''Dreams Of Breathing Underwater''] review in ''[[The Independent]]''\n*[http://arts.guardian.co.uk/filmandmusic/story/0,,2286556,00.html ''Dreams Of Breathing Underwater''] review in 